('25067', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('25067', '2', 'To prepare cake, coat a 12-cup Bundt pan with cooking spray; dust pan with 1 tablespoon flour.'),
('25067', '3', 'Place sugars, cream cheese, and vegetable oil in a large bowl, and beat with a mixer at medium speed until well blended (about 5 minutes).'),
('25067', '4', 'Add eggs and egg whites, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla extract.'),
('25067', '5', 'Lightly spoon 2 1/2 cups flour into dry measuring cups, and level with a knife.'),
('25067', '6', 'Combine 2 1/2 cups flour and next 5 ingredients (2 1/2 cups flour through cinnamon) in a medium bowl, stirring well with a whisk.'),
('25067', '7', 'Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in zucchini, 2/3 cup chocolate chips, and nuts.'),
('25067', '8', 'Pour batter into prepared pan.'),
('25067', '9', 'Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes on a wire rack; remove from pan. Cool completely on wire rack.'),
('25067', '10', 'To prepare glaze, combine 3/4 cup powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa in a small bowl; stir with a whisk.'),
('25067', '11', 'Combine milk, 2 tablespoons chocolate chips, coffee, and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract in a 1-cup glass measure. Microwave at medium 45 seconds or until chocolate melts, stirring after 20 seconds.'),
('25067', '12', 'Combine powdered sugar mixture with chocolate mixture, stirring with a whisk.'),
('25067', '13', 'Drizzle glaze over cake.'),
('25069', '1', 'Gently open each zucchini blossom and nip off the stamen.'),
('25069', '2', 'Place a piece of feta cheese inside each blossom and twist lightly to close.'),
('25069', '3', 'Beat the eggs in a bowl.'),
('25069', '4', 'Spread the bread crumbs in a shallow bowl. Dip each zucchini in the beaten eggs, then dredge in the bread crumbs.'),
('25069', '5', 'Set a large rack over a rimmed baking sheet. In each of 2 large skillets, heat 1/3 cup of the olive oil until shimmering. Carefully lay half of the zucchini in each skillet and fry over moderately high heat until crisp and golden, about 1 1/2 minutes per side.'),
